text.tspan: I am making a picture of a seven set venn diagram.
Every section overlaps every other section in all possible combinations,
If each of the seven sets is a specific color (hex value),
and every section is the average color of the sets that overlap in it,
how can I calculate the colors for all 128 sections?

g.text: First I made sure it understood the problem:

svg.text: can you write a program that does this?

g.text: Then I asked it to make a program:

text.tspan: Now can you write the program,
but instead of outputting a list,
it outputs an .svg file of all the color combinations
as squares, organized by how many colors
so that the rectangles do not overlap?
Then a program that returns a .svg
# Hex color values for each set
the first .svg had all the squares
